cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.ST

The paper discusses a new algorithm for data stream classification, which is a subfield of machine learning. The algorithm involves learning a Mahalanobis metric, which is a technique used in pattern recognition and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of k-NN algorithms and concept drift detection, which are common in data stream analysis, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.ST (Statistics) as possible categories. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed algorithm using specific metrics, indicating cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible category.
